events.name: Western Kentucky Hilltoppers at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Alfred Blue and Kenny Hilliard each scored two touchdowns, and No. 1 LSU overcame a slow start to defeat Western Kentucky 42-9 on Saturday night.

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Brandon Weeden threw for 423 yards and five touchdowns and Joseph Randle ran for three more scores to lead No. 2 Oklahoma State over Texas Tech 66-6 Saturday, making the Cowboys 10-0 for the first time in school history.

events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Trent Richardson rushed for 127 yards and a touchdown, Alabama's defense gave up just 131 total yards and the Crimson Tide (No. 3 BCS, No. 4 AP) beat Mississippi State 24-7 on Saturday night.

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Oregon 53, Stanford 30

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Casey Pachall threw a 25-yard TD pass to Brandon Carter with 1:05 left, then hit Josh Boyce on the go-ahead 2-point conversion, and Boise State's Dan Goodale booted a 39-yard field-goal attempt wide right as time expired to give TCU a 36-35 win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Again? Boise State misses kick, loses to TCU

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Dennis Johnson accounted for 140 total yards and a pair of touchdowns to help No. 8 Arkansas beat Tennessee 49-7 for its sixth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arkansas whips Tenn. to stay alive in SEC West

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Chandler Catanzaro kicked a 43-yard field goal as time expired and No. 9 Clemson rallied from 14 points down in the second half to defeat Wake Forest 31-28 and clinch the ACC Atlantic Division title on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Last-second FG hands Clemson division title

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Capping the worst week in school history, No. 12 Penn State nearly overcame a 17-point deficit but was stopped short on a 4th-and-1 late in a 17-14 loss Saturday to No. 19 Nebraska.

events.name: Florida Gators at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: South Carolina quarterback Connor Shaw ran for 88 yards and two touchdowns to lead South Carolina to a 17-12 win over Florida on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Carolina tops Florida, helps division hopes

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Collin Klein scored on a sneak in the fourth overtime Saturday night, his sixth touchdown of the game, giving Kansas State a dramatic 53-50 victory over Texas A&M.

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw four touchdown passes to surpass Matthew Stafford's school record and No. 14 Georgia romped past No. 24 Auburn 45-7 Saturday, moving within one win of playing for the Southeastern Conference championship.

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Kendial Lawrence topped 100 yards with a touchdown in relief of injured Henry Josey and Missouri's defense kept No. 21 Texas out of the end zone for the first time since 2004 in a 17-5 upset on Saturday that ended a six-game losing streak in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mizzou upsets Texas despite losing RB Josey

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins threw for 260 yards and three touchdowns and 13th-ranked Michigan State beat Iowa 37-21 to take control of the Big Ten's Legends Division.

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Montee Ball broke the Big Ten's single-season touchdown record and 16th-ranked Wisconsin trampled Minnesota 42-13 to keep Paul Bunyan's Axe for the eighth straight year -- and stay in the conference title chase.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wisconsin runs past Minn. to keep Bunyan's Axe

events.name: UCF Knights at Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles

headlines.description: Danny Hrapmann kicked five field goals and Southern Miss (No. 22 BCS, No. 25 AP) narrowly avoided an upset with a 30-29 win over Central Florida on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southern Miss barely survives scare from UCF

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw for 372 yards and led a fourth-quarter touchdown drive that rallied West Virginia to a 24-21 victory Saturday over No. 23 Cincinnati -- which lost both quarterback Zach Collaros and control of the Big East race.
headlines.shortLinkText: QB hurt, Cincy loses to WVU

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Fitzgerald Toussaint ran for 192 yards and a touchdown and backup quarterback Devin Gardner threw a key TD pass to lead No. 22 Michigan past Illinois 31-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson hurt in Michigan's victory over Illinois

events.name: Baylor Bears at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III threw three touchdown passes in a furious fourth-quarter comeback and Baylor escaped with a 31-30 victory Saturday when Kansas failed on a two-point conversion in overtime.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor rallies from 21 back to sink Kansas in OT

events.name: Rice Owls at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Dan Persa threw for a career-high 372 yards, Jeremy Ebert set a personal best with 208 receiving yards and Northwestern beat Rice 28-6 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northwestern's Persa, Ebert post career games

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Tino Sunseri threw for one touchdown and ran for another to lead Pittsburgh to its first road win under new coach Todd Graham, 21-14, over Louisville on Saturday, ending the Cardinals' three-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sunseri's 2 TDs lead Pittsburgh past Louisville

events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at Tulsa Golden Hurricane

headlines.description: Tulsa 59, Marshall 17

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description:
Robert Marve's 1-yard touchdown on a
 quarterback sneak in overtime gave Purdue a 26-23 win over Ohio 
State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marve's sneak lifts Purdue past Ohio St. in OT

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description:
Zac Stacy ran for 135 yards and three
 touchdowns, and Jordan Rodgers threw for 207 yards and two TDs as 
Vanderbilt routed Kentucky 38-8 Saturday in snapping a two-game 
skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Win takes Vanderbilt to verge of bowl eligibility

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Starting quarterback Chase Rettig threw for a touchdown, backup Josh Bordner ran for a score and struggling Boston College held on for a 14-10 win over North Carolina State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Struggling BC holds on to edge out NC State

events.name: Arizona Wildcats at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Rodney Stewart ran for 181 yards and three touchdowns and threw for another, helping Colorado avoid its first winless season at 87-year Folsom Field with a 48-29 win over Arizona Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colorado avoids first winless season at Folsom

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Michael Rocco threw two touchdown passes and Chase Minnifield returned an interception for a touchdown Saturday as Virginia ended a three-game losing streak against Duke with a 31-21 victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Virginia grabs 3rd in a row, ends skid vs. Duke

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Greg Reid scored on an 83-yard punt return and Dustin Hopkins kicked three field goals Saturday to lead Florida State to a 23-19 win over longtime nemesis Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reid return TD, 3 FGs lift Florida St. past Miami

events.name: Washington Huskies at USC Trojans

headlines.shortLinkText: McNeal nabs career high in yards as USC rolls

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Isi Sofele rushed for a career-high 190 yards and one touchdown, quarterback Zach Maynard threw for one score and ran for another, and California beat Oregon State 23-6 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sofele rushes for 190, TD as Cal is bowl eligible

events.name: UCLA Bruins at Utah Utes

headlines.description: John White rushed for 167 yards and scored three touchdowns and Conroy Black returned an interception 67 yards for another score to lift Utah to a 31-6 victory over UCLA on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah wipes away UCLA to become bowl eligible

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Jonas Gary ran for a career-high 136 yards and two touchdowns, and Notre Dame made itself right at home against skidding Maryland in a 45-21 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notre Dame pastes Maryland to win 3rd in a row

events.name: Louisiana Tech Bulldogs at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Chad Boyd and Javontay Crowe scored defensive touchdowns, and Matt Nelson added a pair of field goals, helping Louisiana Tech rally for a 27-7 win Saturday night over Mississippi.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ole Miss loses to La. Tech for 5th straight defeat
